<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Guide1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Guide,</orth> subst. one who directs another in his way or course: <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.183" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 1, 183</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.3.6" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 3, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.3.25" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 3, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.116" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 116</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.190" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 190</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.205" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 205</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.13.145" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 13, 145</bibl>. <emph>give them g. to us</emph> == show them in, <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.252" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 252</bibl>. Sing. for the plur.: <cit><quote>Love and Fortune be my gods, my g.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 351" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 351</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>if my instructions may be your g.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.181" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 2, 181</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>